article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- — Jordan Ivy-Curry's 22 points helped UTSA defeat Prairie View A&M 103-89 on Thursday. Ivy-Curry added eight assists for the Roadrunners (6-7). Carlton Linguard added 16 points while going 5 of 10 from the floor, including 0 for 4 from 3-point range, and 6 for 7 from the line, and he also had 10 rebounds and three blocks. Christian Tucker had 16 points and was 3 of 6 shooting, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 8 for 9 from the line. The Panthers (5-7) were led in scoring by Chris Felix Jr., who finished with 19 points and two steals. Javontae Hopkins added 15 points and 14 rebounds for Prairie View A&M. Charles Lane Jr. also had 15 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
